# `examples/alphabet_sort/rl.toml` - RL Training Config for Alphabet Sort with SWE-like Agentic Env
- Orchestrates multi-turn, RL training via a custom Agentic environment configured to perform alphabet sorting tasks;
- Enforces progressive learning rollout instructions using power per turn and max turns (3-5 turns) to foster multi-step reasoning;
- Facilitates training `Qwen/Qwen3-4B-Instruct-2507` with LoRA regularization (alpha=64), optimized for single-H100 GPU or cluster scalability;
- Supports GLM-5/Trinity/MoE MoE models and other causal LMs;
- Integrates with multi-node deployment via Slurm/Kubernetes orchestration for isolated subsets of training data per node.
```
